<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-06-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-06-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="503" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d503">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Wharton</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                        Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-06-27"><hi rend="italic">June 27,
                                1891</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 25th instant in relation to the proposed
                            Behring Sea arbitration, and to inform you that I transmitted a copy of
                            it to the Marquis of Salisbury by the mail of the 26th.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Julian
                            Pauncefote</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>